tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 20, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104dom1695191702402.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dom1695191702402.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/dom1695191702402.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"lbd1665702658346\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Macro Definitions\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The translation table compiler supports up to ten macros, ^M0 through ^M9, for commonly-used combinations.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__p_d64556e1_d64557e1_d64558e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">M</code> can be uppercase or lowercase. For example, the following assignments map ^M0 to the PF1 key on a VT200 keyboard, and the combinations PF1 A and PF1 a to the Uniface ^ACCEPT function:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^escOP ^M0 PF1 7 bits mode\n^M0^aA ^ACCEPT\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__p_d64559e1_d64560e1_d64561e1\">Using another macro or the uppercase or lowercase function within a macro definition is not supported. The following macro definitions are not supported:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^M3^escP ^M5 INCORRECT nested macro\n^esc^aA ^M4 INCORRECT upper/lowercase code\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__note_w1895ab1b5b9_w1896ab1b5_w1897ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> You must define the macro before you use it.</div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__section_cmq_5rs_vyb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d519177e70\"> Several output sequences per macro </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__p_d64565e1_d64566e1_d64567e1\">Up to three different output sequences can be assigned to\n        each macro. This capability is particularly useful when the keyboard can operate in several\n        modes. The translation table compiler then generates a separate assignment for each sequence\n        assigned to the macro.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__p_d64568e1_d64569e1_d64570e1\">For example, a VT200 keyboard can operate in seven bits,\n        eight bits, and eight bits with seven bits input. The input sequence (in the keyboard\n        translation table) is different for each mode. The following macro definitions assign all\n        three possible combinations for the PF1 key to macro ^M0. The combinations PF1 E and PF1 e\n        are recognized as ^ERASE in all three keyboard modes. The lines generated are shown\n        below:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__pre_gn5_wrs_vyb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^escOP ^M0 PF1 7 bits mode\n^143P ^M0 PF1 8 bits mode\n^015P ^M0 PF1 8 bits mode with 7 bit input\n^M0^eE ^ERASE\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__p_d64571e1_d64572e1_d64573e1\">This is equivalent to (but much more concise than):</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__pre_hn5_wrs_vyb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">^escOPe ^ERASE\n^escOPE ^ERASE\n^143Pe ^ERASE\n^143PE ^ERASE\n^015Pe ^ERASE\n^015PE ^ERASE</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__p_d64574e1_d64575e1_d64576e1\">If a source sequence contains more than one macro, each\n        macro must be assigned the same number of combinations.</p>\n<div class=\"note caution note_caution\" id=\"lbd1665702658346__note_in5_wrs_vyb\"><span class=\"note__title\">CAUTION:</span> The total number of bytes assigned to all macros\n        together must not exceed 450 bytes.</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4809770\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_4809770\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Macro Definitions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 20, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Macro Definitions The translation table compiler supports up to ten macros, ^M0 through ^M9, for commonly-used combinations. The M can be uppercase or lowercase. For example, the following assignments map ^M0 to the PF1 key on a VT200 keyboard, and the combinations PF1 A and PF1 a to the Uniface ^ACCEPT function: ^escOP ^M0 PF1 7 bits mode ^M0^aA ^ACCEPT Copy Using another macro or the uppercase or lowercase function within a macro definition is not supported. The following macro definitions are not supported: ^M3^escP ^M5 INCORRECT nested macro ^esc^aA ^M4 INCORRECT upper/lowercase code Copy Note: You must define the macro before you use it. Several output sequences per macro Up to three different output sequences can be assigned to each macro. This capability is particularly useful when the keyboard can operate in several modes. The translation table compiler then generates a separate assignment for each sequence assigned to the macro. For example, a VT200 keyboard can operate in seven bits, eight bits, and eight bits with seven bits input. The input sequence (in the keyboard translation table) is different for each mode. The following macro definitions assign all three possible combinations for the PF1 key to macro ^M0. The combinations PF1 E and PF1 e are recognized as ^ERASE in all three keyboard modes. The lines generated are shown below: ^escOP ^M0 PF1 7 bits mode ^143P ^M0 PF1 8 bits mode ^015P ^M0 PF1 8 bits mode with 7 bit input ^M0^eE ^ERASE Copy This is equivalent to (but much more concise than): ^escOPe ^ERASE ^escOPE ^ERASE ^143Pe ^ERASE ^143PE ^ERASE ^015Pe ^ERASE ^015PE ^ERASE Copy If a source sequence contains more than one macro, each macro must be assigned the same number of combinations. CAUTION: The total number of bytes assigned to all macros together must not exceed 450 bytes. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}